sentences: Florin Niculescu (born February 8, 1967 in Bucharest) is a Romanian violinist of Romani (Gypsy) ethnicity.
He received his first violin lessons from his father, with whom he started to study seriously when he was 4–5 years old.
In 1991 he left for Paris to fulfill his dream of meeting Grappelli and making a name in jazz.
In 1995 he joined Romane's band, and in 2001 he was invited by Biréli Lagrène to join his Gipsy Project inspired by the Quintette du Hot Club de France.
